Gulley has 16 years' experience delivering legal advice as both an in-house and private practice lawyer in Australia and the United Kingdom.  He is recognised as a "Rising Star" in Technology, Media & Telecommunications in Doyles' Guide for 2016. Gulley's expertise includes advising on:

•	large-scale outsourcing, cloud computing and managed services initiatives;
•	complex IT transformation projects; 
•	systems and software development, integration, licensing and support models;
•	data privacy and security;
•	big data and analytics projects; and the appointment of suppliers to provide IT hardware, software licensing, software development, software support services, cloud services and IT professional services; and 
•	the appointment of suppliers to provide IT hardware, software licensing, software development, software support services, cloud services and IT professional services.

jobs.description:
On assignment in the Victorian Department of Education and Training.  A member of the Commercial Law Unit serving Departmental Divisions and Schools.  In this role I provide broad ranging commercial legal support including:
- Advising on general commercial contracts and contract disputes – goods and services contracts;
- Negotiating RFQ/RFP, tender and procurement agreements;
- Negotiating IP Licences, property Licences;
- Negotiating MoUs – research, inter-department projects, 3rd party service suppliers;
- Negotiating Confidentiality Deeds, Settlement Deeds;
- Advising on compliance with Privacy And Data Protection Act and Information Privacy Principles.

Consulting to a number of corporate clients of Plexus Legal requiring a blend of legal experience and experience in managing change and achieving operational efficiency within legal teams:
•	Reporting on opportunities for strategic IT investment, business process improvement, efficiency gains and cost savings within a legal department;
•	Project managing a legal initiative to simplify of a suite of customer facing documentation – including identifying effective communication channels and plain language re-drafting of significant quantity of terms & conditions – focusing on efficiency and a better customer experience;
•	Reporting on opportunities for transformational business change and additional process improvement and Lean/Six Sigma initiatives within a legal team;
•	Providing annual reporting for a legal team that tracks progress of multiple initiatives, measuring benefits to the organisation and provide recommendations for further initiatives to guide future change planning;
•	Planning and documenting project initiation for a legal team - conducting performance gap analysis, building business case to gain organisational support for legal initiatives, recommending initiatives to deliver greatest operational efficiencies and identifying key risks to success.

Worked closely with Head of Strategic Risk to lead the legal team during period of transition.
Provided commercial, pragmatic legal risk management covering a broad range of commercial and regulatory legal matters - general commercial, IT and IP, vendor management and contract life cycle management, compliance, M&A and dispute resolution;
Re-built key stakeholder confidence in the management and capability of the legal team;
Was an exampler of customer-centric service delivery; 
Established foundations for effective legal service delivery:
o	business performance management framework to record and analysis of legal work;
o	transparent operational processes for efficient and effective allocation and performance of work;
o	cultural change - prioritising work of high value to the business, customer focus and collaboration.

general.description:
I am a property lawyer in the Brisbane office of MinterEllison. I specialise in the acquisition, leasing and disposal of real estate assets in Queensland and Australia. I have experience acting for a wide range of clients in the commercial, industrial, retail and resources sectors.

My main areas of practice are:
•	major real estate transactions;
•	property development;
•	commercial leasing;
•	land access; and
•	general property advice.

Mark is a specialist property lawyer with extensive experience in the following areas:

•	commercial, industrial, rural and retail leasing;

•	industrial, commercial and residential property development;

•	acquisitions and disposals;

•	strata and community development; and

•	general property related work.

